==Swedish==

===Verb===
'''vicka'''
#[[wiggle]]; [[wobble]]; [[tilt]]
#:''Hon '''vickade''' på tårna.''
#::"She wiggled her toes."
#:''Om man '''vickar''' på det här locket tillräckligt länge går det av.''
#::"If you move this lid up and down long enough, it will break (off)."
#{{sv-colloquial}} act as [[substitute]], [[stand-in]], temporarily fill the position of
#:''Hon '''vickade''' som lärare förra året.''
#::"She worked as a substitute teacher last year."

====Etymology====
'''wiggle'''

Since 1689 from the dialectal word ''vicka'' "yield; bend sideways; run in a waddling fashion". Most likely related to ''[[veck]]'' "[[fold]]; [[crease]] (noun)" and ''[[vika]]'' "fold (verb)".

'''act as substitute'''

Short for [[vikariera]]

